<P>
   BOILER-ROOMS (Los Angeles) _ It took just a telephone call to
sweet talk Jeff Daly out of $20,000. A smooth telemarketer promised
the Agua Dulce man up to a 400 percent profit if he invested in a
film called ``Operation: Desert Gold,'' he says. So he forked over
the money, unaware he was joining the ranks of people who
prosecutors say are defrauded in telemarketing scams, many of them
now based in L.A.'s San Fernando Valley. Daly's case is not unique.
In Los Angeles alone, during a 1998 federal crackdown about 20
boiler-room operations were identified including ``Operation:
Desert Gold,'' federal officials said. By Phillip W. Browne. (Will
move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news file.)
