<P>
   SUBURBIA-FENCES (Undated) _ A new range war has broken out, this
time on the suburban frontier. As in days of old, it concerns
fences _ specifically, wooden stockade fences, which are growing in
popularity and lend a touch of Fort Apache to even the most
unremarkable ranch home. By Patricia Leigh Brown. With photo.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 2:30 p.m. ET in `a' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   YANKEES-ZIMMER (Tampa, Fla.) _ Don Zimmer seems to have known
everyone and seen everything in his half century in baseball as a
player, coach and manager. Now, at 68 years old, he is filling in
for his close friend Joe Torre, the Yankees' manager, who learned
last week that he had prostate cancer. No one knows whether it will
be for three weeks or three months, and Zimmer's mission is to
maintain the winning culture Torre has created. By Buster Olney.
With photo.
</P>
