   CAMBODIA-TA-MOK (Phnom Penh) _ In the harsh politics of Cambodia
today, it is possible that the peasant general Ta Mok will in the
end be the only Khmer Rouge leader called to account for the deaths
of more than a million people between 1975 and 1979. By Seth
Mydans.
</P>
