   BOLIVIA-BANZER (La Paz, Bolivia) _ While Chile's Gen. Augusto
Pinochet awaits his fate in London, another of Latin America's
former dictators, Hugo Banzer of Bolivia, now the country's elected
president, is also coming under scrutiny for his part in a ``dirty
war'' against leftists in the 1970s. By Clifford Krauss.
</P>
<P>
   BOSTON-SCHOOLS (Boston) _ As Boston inches toward a new effort
to build more schools in minority neighborhoods, some worry that
simmering racial antagonism will burst forth again. By Steven A.
Holmes. With photo.
</P>
