<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    NBA EAST NOTES: The way of the Bison
 &HT;    By Jeffrey Denberg
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   And how was your week? Detroit center Bison Dele's wasn't so
hot.
</P>
<P>
   The former Brian Williams missed the team bus and had to take a
cab to a game in Orlando on March 6. He said he did not get his
wake-up call. Pistons PR chief Matt Dobek said he called Dele's
room and got no answer. Dele was fined $1,000.
</P>
<P>
   He played horribly that night, missing 11 of 17 shots and giving
up a season-high 23 to Ike Austin. The folks in Orlando were not
fooled by his name change _ they knew it was the guy they drafted
out of Arizona and watched struggle through two horrible seasons.
Every time he touched the ball they played the soundtrack of a cow
mooing.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's the worst place for me,'' Dele said. ``I have never
played well down there. Just too much bad blood.''
</P>
<P>
   Monday against the Wizards he was 1-for-5, and benched in the
fourth quarter of a close game. Wednesday, Dele was ejected from a
game in Washington. He got the boot from rookie ref Marc Davis in
the third. He grabbed a rebound and swung around, nearly hitting
Ben Wallace with his elbows. Davis thought the play was
intentional.
</P>
<P>
   ``I never touched him,'' Dele said. ``He called it for reading
my mind.''
</P>
<P>
   No fine for Iverson
</P>
<P>
   All that brotherly love is fading among Philadelphia's 76ers,
with under-performing Tim Thomas dealt to Milwaukee and Allen
Iverson blowing off practice without so much as an ``excuse me.''
</P>
<P>
   Coach Larry Brown revealed this isn't the first practice Iverson
has missed, and the maximum fine for a multiple offender can be as
much as $5,000 for each offense. However, after two team meetings
Friday, the Sixers' players said they were satisfied with their
teammate's excuse and voted not to discipline him. Iverson said he
missed practice because he was attending to his girlfriend, Tawanna
Turner.
</P>
<P>
   ``My girl was sick,'' Iverson said. ``She had a miscarriage
recently. We've got kids TiauraAllen IIand I had to handle that.
I'll handle any repercussions. ... I called when it happened. I was
on my way out the door.''
</P>
<P>
   Without Ewing againPatrick Ewing Charles OakleyTerry Cummings
Buck Williams Chris Dudley''
</P>
<P>
   The Rice aftermathAlonzo MourningGlen RiceGeorge ShinnEddie
JonesElden Campbellbecomes the highest-paid player in Hornets
history with 4 1/2 seasons left on the seven-year, $49 million deal
he got from the Lakers. And because he was traded, his contract
increases by $5.25 million.
</P>
<P>
   Suddenly the go-to guyToni KukocTim Floyd''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
