 &HT;    NBA WEST NOTES: Of Clippers and Kings
 &HT;    By Jeffrey Denberg
 &HT;    c. 1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   On the threshold of what might have been total disaster, the
L.A. Clippers can smile a little. They met the one opponent they
had a real chance to beat over the next week and a half and they
finally won, beating Sacramento 106-92 Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   The Clips beat the Kings three times last season. In fact, their
last victory before Thursday's came vs. the Kings, on the final day
of the '97-98 season. The Clips had lost 10 straight before that
game and 17 in a row to open this season, tying Miami's 11-year-old
record for early-season futility.Chris Ford
</P>
<P>
   ``Looking at our upcoming schedule, we knew (Thursday) was going
to be the one we really had to get,'' guard Darrick Martin
</P>
