<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HKN-NEXT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COMPARING THE GREAT ONES 
EDITORS: CHART WITH GRETZKY
</HEADLINE>
 GREAT ONE-TEX (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MIKE HEIKA 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Player Yr Games Goals Assists PPG Best postseason Eric Lindros 7
423 260 334 1.4 26 pts, 1997 Mike Modano 10 696 305 420 1.04 20
pts, 1991 Paul Kariya 5 285 158 200 1.26 13 pts, 1997 Teemu Selanne
7 468 303 317 1.32 10 pts, 1997 Jaromir Jagr 9 645 332 501 1.29 24
pts, 1992
THE NEXT ONES
ERIC LINDROS Defining moments: 1995 Hart Trophy winner as MVP, but
had a meltdown in 1997 Stanley Cup Finals when Philadelphia was
swept by Detroit. Wayne's World: Lindros has all the tools to be
the next superstar and was originally dubbed ``The Next One.'' But
his pouty refusal to play in Quebec has never been forgotten by
many fans. He's still criticized for not being a leader.
</P>
<P>
   JAROMIR JAGR Defining moments: Helped Pittsbrugh win the Stanley
Cup in 1991 and 1992 and helped Czech Republic win the Olympic gold
medal in 1998. Wayne's World: Jagr has the talent and personality
to be the league's next great salesman. However, he plays for a
financially struggling franchise in Pittsburgh and likely has no
shot at a championship there. A trade to a major media market (New
York, Los Angeles) could vault him to the top.
</P>
<P>
   PAUL KARIYA Defining moments: Is only 24 years old and has three
times been selected the best left winger in the NHL. Wayne's World:
Gretzky was Kariya's hero growing up, and the similarity in their
style is spooky. But Kariya will not be The Next One because he's
uncomfortable with the spotlight.
</P>
<P>
   MIKE MODANO Defining moments: Helped Team USA win the 1996 World
Cup and helped the Stars become the NHL's best regular-season team
last season and this season. Wayne's World: Modano is everything
the NHL needs: good-looking, well-spoken, fun to watch. However, he
would just as soon be playing golf, and it's tough to sell that.
</P>
<P>
   TEEMU SELANNE Defining moments: Scored 76 goals in his rookie
season, an NHL record. His trade from Winnipeg Jets to the Mighty
Ducks of Anaheim in 1996 made him Southern California's top hockey
salesman. Wayne's World: Selanne is to Kariya what Ted Lindsay was
to Gordie Howe. Selanne might be better than his partner at times,
but he'll never get the same recognition.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-03-13-99 2007EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
