<P>
   &QL; 
AMWEST _ A pay dispute between flight attendants and America West
Airlines, smoldering since the company's 1991 financial meltdown,
has left negotiators with little time to defuse the animosity and
work out a deal before Friday's strike deadline. Though there have
been signs of hope for a settlement, the 2,400 flight attendants
are toting some heavy baggage born of America West's bankruptcy
filing seven years ago. The Tempe-based carrier cut their pay 10
percent and left them holding worthless stock in its reorganization
_ stock that the flight attendants were forced to buy with salaries
as little as $12,000 a year. By PETER CORBETT. Story will move in
the ``A'' category. &QL;
